<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98382913360427></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98382913360427><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98382913360427>RE: Imbue spells</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98382913360427#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6567><span id= >Nitsujlak</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>163 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 5th 4:52 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You get them from your local general spell vendor. Each imbue spell is usuable by only certain shaman following certain gods. For example for ogre shaman following rallos zek you get imbue jade. The use of this spell is to imbue gems to be used in smithing to make god/race/class specific armors.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
