<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98357917028675></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98357917028675><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98357917028675>How to solo a Shaman lvl 34+</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98357917028675#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 2nd 7:26 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At lvl 34 Shaman get a pet,and thus experance the last major change in their lives.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>I know of 4 ways to solo a shaman afte lvl 34.  <br><br>Methood 1  Pet Kiting<br><br>Methood 2 Root and Dot.<br><br>Methood 3 Pet Attack.  <br><br>Methood 4 Shaman Soloing.  <br><br>When my shaman was near lvl 40 I spent some time comparing actual damage done by diffrent weapons.  I also took the time to determain the percent damage done by Dots, Melee, and the pet during combat.  One of the weapons I was playing around with was the JCP.  On avg. the pet did 50% of the damage, the dot did 25% and the weapon did 25%.  <br><br>Methood 1<br>This is kiting the mob while the  pet attacks it.  This methood dose not develop important shmaan skills and it is limited as to where it can be used.  Also Dots do 25% less damage if the target is moving.  I personaly recomend against this methood.  <br><br>Methood 2.  <br>Cast Root Dot the mob and med until it is time to recast.  This methood has its uses but dose not use two of the shaman weapons.  The pet and the weapon.  Also it is limited in where it can be used.  <br><br>Methood 3. <br>This methood involves buffing up the pet with all the melee buff, Slowing and rooting the mob.  Sick the pet on the mob, and then dot the mob and heal the pet as needed.  This methood was more popular before Totemic Armor and other good melee equipment was in the game for shamans.<br><br>Methood 4.  <br>This is the methood I recomand for meleeing a shaman.  Find a safe spot to park your pet.  Self buff, and buff the pet with sow, str, and speed.  Pull the mob with slow.  Run back to the pet and sick it on the mob.  The pet may or may not stop the mob's charge.  Cast sickness dot.  If the pet is holding the mob it may come of at this time.  Cast Poision Dot on the mob.  If the mob has not come off the pet yet, it will now.  Melee the mob until it is dead.  In this methood the primary job of the shaman is to take damage while the pet and dots do most of the damage.  Therefore High AC is ver important.  <br><br>While soloing you need to use all your skill and wits.  I often use one of the other methoods in combanation with shaman soloing if the mob is near my soloing limit.  <br><br>For example pet kit the mob after health and mana are low.  And Root and dot the mob after it has killd the pet. However most mobs I can solo I can solo by methood 4 and I can do it inside or outside.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
