	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with most of what you said, However, For most shaman I suggest putting all points into wisdom.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can buff every other stat.  <br><br>If you want to melee, weapon choice is much more inportant than race.  In a group the shaman is not going to be the one taking damage.  With a good weapon you can do as much or more damage than your best dot up to lvl 49.  At higher lvls you will need to use 2hb weapons to do this type of damage. <br><br>When soloing having natural regen may cut down on down time.  I also recomend that for soloing you focus on damage instead of AC.  Get the highest damage weapon you can and keep your skill high.  <br>At lvl 46 I could kill a frost giant scout in less than 42 sec.  Before VoS ran out<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
