	   <tr><td colspan=2>Our dots stack, so there is no reason why you can't cast during group combat.&nbsp;&nbsp;The makeup of the group and your role within that group would be the deciding factor.  To start, I will slow and throw my two best dots on the mob, then watch the progress of the group before I allocate further mana to dots or dd's.  If the situation starts to get hairy, I'll cast shock of the tainted (230 instant dmg) or gale of poison (122 dmg x 3) once or twice to lower hp's quickly.<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>54 Barbarian Shaman (Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>35 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
