<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98340109680307></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98340109680307><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98340109680307>How I soloed my shaman lvl 1-13</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98340109680307#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 28th 5:58 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I hunted near the guards until I got enough money to by the lvl 1 dd (burst of flame I think).&nbsp;&nbsp;I then would stand against the canyon wall and cast the dd on mobs as they went by.  I then beat them to death with my cracked staff.  <br><br>Thoughts on Buffing.<br>I always buffed inner fire and Str, dex, and agi after i got the spells.  <br><br>Thoughts on Armor.<br>I learned to tailor and made a full set of PW armor.  For a shaman armor makes a real differance.  I could fight multipul mobs while others (with no or little armor) had to run to the guards.  You should up grade your armor by doing quests and buying Banded, until you have a full set of banded.  <br><br>Tricks of the Traid.  <br>Obtain the spell Flash of Light.  This spell is very fast and blinds the target.  I could hunt the goblin villages early by casting FoL on one of the scouts who would then run away, and not retrun until the other scout was dead or near dead.  Also it is a great (pre sow) excape spell.  Casting it on the mob that is beating you to death may give you enough of a head start to make it to a guard.  Also it is a good way to increase your Div skill so you get a lot less fizzles when you can cast Snake eyes.  The higher your Div skill the better your inv spell will work so cast spell of this type as often as you can.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
