	   <tr><td colspan=2>BS Tunic is a nice piece.&nbsp;&nbsp; I remember getting mine at around your lvl (a gift from guild mate) and loving that it looked so different from the banded.  By lvl 40 I was tired of it, and ready to move on to something new.<br><br>The undead knight in the tower in Unrest is a lvl 28 bad boy (to your lvl 24, that is).  If you want to camp this piece rather than buy it, plan on having a few friends with you.  Also, if you have a druid friend who can go with you and share wolf form, your trek into the manor will be much easier and without aggro (or find yourself a pally pal who can cast IvU).  If you have never hunted in Unrest, I would suggest that you do some studying up on it and printing maps before going in.<br><br>Your other option, of course, would be to buy one.  I am not sure what they run for, as I have never purchased one, but I do see them auctioned rather frequently in EC (Norrath's largest over-priced mall, IMHO).<br><br>Good luck getting your tunic!<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>54 Barbarian Shaman (Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>35 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
