	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes the 50% dose make it hard to get skill up.&nbsp;&nbsp;And the damage cap on the BFH makes it no better than a RTS and wors than a FS staff as far as damage gose.  <br><br>As for 2HB being out for shaman, look at some of the 2hb weapons, some have very nice wis or mana bonus. <br><br>Finaly being a "Caster" is only one choice for playing the shaman class. There are two reasions for the popularity of spears as shaman weapons.  <br>1. The epic shaman is a spear.  <br>2. How easy it is to get a JCP and a CGS.  Are these the best weapons for shaman? No, they are just the easyest to get good shaman weapons and shields.  Therefor that is what all the twinks end up with and what all the nontwinks aspire to.  <br><br>And as has been said many times before, wis is not the end all and be all of being a shaman.  Dragon raids and other such events are the only time that having a very high wis helps a party.  One big fight winner take all and the healers better have the mana.  Even then Magic resistance is more important.  I have never been on a raid where there was a min set on wis.  For MR yes for CR yes, for FR yes.   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
