	   <tr><td colspan=2>they about covered it. But your weapon choice is really all up to you and your playing style. For those shaman who like to paly like secondary clerics and just read their books and stand for a heal or buff every so often, piercing and only piercing is the way to go (then again for this type of player weapons dont really matter all that much) For those of you who want to solo a lot, and get in the fray of the battle 2hb or 1hb is the way to go. Now, if you're like me, you like to mix it all up. I like to be able to tank when i want (not very often but i can), heal, have plenty of mana, when im outta mana be able to do some serious damage, and just plain out look cool doing all of this. So what i did was practice ALL weapon skills. why you ask? because there are some great items for shm in peircing, 1hb AND 2hb. I personally plan on getting my hands on a Ringed Mace of the Ykesha, Blight Hammer of the Scourge, and lastly the beutifal god-like Spear of Fate. All of these are very high end items. But if you really like that shm you chose to play, planning ahead is a BIG thing to do. <br>my 2 cp<br>Please Rate My posts, i like input on my advice =)<br>Nitsujlak Barshemguud Ogre shm of war<br>Prexus Server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
