	   <tr><td colspan=2>Shaman doesn't mean a man who is 'sha.'&nbsp;&nbsp;Think of it as being someone associated with 'Shama,' although that's not the real etymology either.  You wouldn't say Romen to refer to the citizens of Rome, would you?  They're Romans.  Likewise, the plural of shaman is shamans.<br><br>And if they're "the only magic using class of the barbarians, ogres and trolls," all those ogre and troll shadowknights are going to be rather annoyed that they can't cast their spells any more.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
